comment: LATR shows that Westbrook (OKC) does not go through Dragic's (MIA) space. Dragic established legal guarding position and the contact is considered incidental.
Bosh (MIA) splits his feet on the perimeter at the start of his drive.
Roberson (OKC) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Waiters (OKC) jumps in the air to defend the shot attempt and would have avoided any contact with Wade (MIA) if Wade had not jumped into Waiters.
Ibaka (OKC) legally contests Bosh's (MIA) jump shot attempt.
Ibaka (OKC) sets the screen on Winslow (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Waiters (OKC) maintains legal guarding position and does not affect Wade's (MIA) RSBQ at the start of the drive.
Ibaka (OKC) sets the screen on Winslow (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Ibaka (OKC) makes contact with Wade's (MIA) body that affects his driving layup attempt.
Wade (MIA) maintains legal guarding position as he contests Westbrook's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
